  </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Shaman Stop Screwing Each Other Over!</span><hr size=1> Ok, I just read about another Hole raid that was not able to kill High Scale Kirn for the shaman epic because he was not up. He wasn't up because the group that killed him earlier for another shaman couldn't take ten seconds to kill his pet!<br>
<br>
Kirn's spawn time is rumored to be around 4-5 hours. Some have said that they've killed the pet and then Kirn has popped for them soon after. Others have said they've seen two pets up at the same time.<br>
<br>
One thing is for certain, kill the stupid dog after you kill Kirn and the next shaman to come along should have no problem.<br>
<br>
Now there's always going to be some inconsiderate idiot who leaves the pet up. To protect yourself, four to five hours before the raid, take your lvl1 Halfling Brell rogue and go down there yourself to see if Kirn or his pet is up. If only the pet is up, try to /petition a guide to kill the pet. I don't know why a guide would do this but some people have said they will sometimes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usagemonprayeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sagemon Prayeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/16/01 3:04:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shaman Stop Screwing Each Other Over!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> To protect yourself, four to five hours before the raid, take your lvl1 Halfling Brell rogue and go down there yourself to see if Kirn or his pet is up. If only the pet is up, try to /petition a guide to kill the pet. I don't know why a guide would do this but some people have said they will sometimes. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I didn't think of petitioning.  I had scouted the zone with my rogue and saw the problem, so we got down to the undead tower and killed the pet as quick as we could.  (It's a skeleton, not a dog, btw.)  Kirn spawned after about two and a half hours.  Unfortunately, a lot of people needed to log by then, so we had to go after Kirn with a small force.  We were pretty tired and made a mistake, so we failed.  I'd be interested to hear whether petitioning would have worked, because this is the second time the pet bug has bitten one of our raids.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I hope that Kanin's post will plant a seed in the mind of all raiders.  If you're on a raid that kills Kirn, be sure to have the pullers get that stupid skeleton!  No more stupid pet tricks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utoein.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toein</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/16/01 6:42:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shaman Stop Screwing Each Other Over!</span><hr size=1> /cheer Kanin<br>
